Why 99: Directly answers "did this release hurt us?" — the question every engineering org asks but rarely has automated tooling to answer from the database layer.

5. Capacity Forecasting with Confidence Intervals
Where: Warehouse Health, Cost & Contract What: Use 90-day historical metering to project when each warehouse will exceed its current capacity (based on p95 queue time trending upward). Show:

Days until queue pressure becomes sustained (>5 queries queued for >30s)
Days until current budget is exhausted at current burn rate
Confidence interval (67% and 95%)
-- Linear regression on 90-day p95 queue time
WITH daily_p95 AS (...),
regression AS (
  SELECT REGR_SLOPE(p95_queue_sec, day_number) AS slope,
         REGR_INTERCEPT(p95_queue_sec, day_number) AS intercept,
         REGR_R2(p95_queue_sec, day_number) AS r2
  FROM daily_p95
)
-- Project days until p95 crosses threshold
SELECT (threshold - intercept) / NULLIF(slope, 0) AS days_until_threshold
Why 99: Shifts from reactive ("warehouse is queuing now") to predictive ("warehouse will queue in 12 days at current trajectory"). Leadership loves time-to-action forecasts.

